This article highlights President Obama's commitment to serving veterans and the work that has been done over the past seven and a half years to fulfill that commitment. The article mentions several accomplishments, including delivering more healthcare, providing timely benefits, expanding research on Post-Traumatic Stress and Traumatic Brain Injury, and helping veterans with education and employment opportunities. It also announces two major milestones: cutting veteran homelessness by nearly half since 2010 and enrolling 500,000 veterans in the Million Veteran Program. The article discusses the administration's focus on five core areas of service to veterans: health care, benefits, homelessness, economic opportunity, and resources and transformation at the VA. It emphasizes the need for ongoing support and reform to better serve veterans.